article.description: Kalisha Keane and Porsche Poole each scored 16 points and Michigan State (No. 22 ESPN/USA Today, No. 25 AP) rolled to an 82-42 win over Detroit Mercy on Sunday.
article.headline: Kalisha Keane, Porsche Poole help MSU roll past Detroit Mercy
article.linkText: Keane, Poole help MSU roll past Detroit Mercy
article.story:
EAST LANSING, Mich. -- Kalisha Keane and Porsche Poole each scored 16 points and Michigan State (No. 22 ESPN/USA Today, No. 25 AP) rolled to an 82-42 win over Detroit Mercy on Sunday.

Keane hit four 3-pointers to lead a balanced Spartans offense that had four players in double figures. She also had six rebounds, five assists and two steals for Michigan State (3-1).

Annalise Pickrel added 13 points, while Taylor Alton scored 10 points in 10 minutes for Michigan State, which was coming off a 26-point loss to second-ranked Baylor on Friday.

Sophomore guard Demeisha Fambro led the way for the Titans (3-1), who entered the contest 3-0 for the first time since 1991-92 season. Fambro scored 14 points, while Yar Shayok added 11.
